

step1:- create or single or multiple context as per project structure
tip:- create single file or multiple files for each context, make sure to create it either top of component in case of single file or in external file and export it

eg:- const ExampleContext = createContext() => import from react


step2:- create provider, again either in single file or in multiple file
tip:- create multiple files for multiple providers according to their structure, import the context ad its very import to have provider in structure

eg:- <ExampleContext.Provider value={value}>  => value is a json containing all the required data to be reused


step3:- for consuming the context provider either you can use them directly importing the useContext or you can make hook for it
tip:- create customHooks in order make the structure clean


step4:- now use the importedContext or custom hook containing the context

const {requiredData} = useContext(importedContext)
or const {requiredData} = useCustomContextHook() 



